        (794, 'IDO TEA Willowy tea 30 tea bags', 'IDOTEA Store', 'From the brand Previous page Background       The CEO of IDO has crafted a distinct range of fermented traditional teas, inspired by her personal journey with Narcolepsy and the guidance of a specialist in Korean traditional medicine. After successfully treating her condition with Korean herbal remedies, she was motivated to create a comprehensive collection of herbal teas that could be savored by all, without any unpleasant herbaceous odors or flavors. Why is IDO unique?       While many Asian tea companies choose to use traditional ingredients or produce fermented green tea, most brands do not ferment traditional tea ingredients. IDO, however, has dedicated years to cultivating their own crops and undergoing thorough research and development to create products that not only maximize nutritional value but are highly palatable, despite their bold choice of unfamiliar ingredients. Where is it produced?       IDOs herbs are harvested from a plantation in the idyllic town of ChungHaMeon, located in Pohang city, Korea. Nestled near a pine tree planted during the reign of King Sejong, the region is known for its pure and clear atmosphere, providing the perfect environment for nurturing high-quality herbs. IDO - What does it mean?       IDOs ingredients have been thoughtfully chosen by a highly respected herb specialist and Oriental wellness practitioner with over 17 years of experience, ensuring that our products provide the best possible support for your well-being. Next page Product Description Maintaining optimal wellness requires a balance between physical (posture and exercise), chemical (diet), and mental (stress and social) factors. However, in todays fast-paced world, it can be challenging to consistently consume fresh, home-cooked meals. IDO offers a solution with its tea adapted from ingredients traditionally used for wellness commonly, thus removing the potential for side effects or over consump