a continually strives to improve product quality. As part of its commitment to transparency, Aiya undergoes annual third-party audits and holds multiple international certifications for its pure Matcha green tea. These certifications include: GFSI (FSSC 22000 by Bureau Veritas), AIB (Superior), JAS Organic by OMIC, NOP Organic by QAI, Halal, Kosher, Gluten-Free, and Non-GMO Project Verified. Next page Product Description Aiya’s Matcha To Go sticks pack a unique blend of traditional Ceremonial Grade Matcha into a convenient single-serving stick. Simply add one stick to cold or hot water, then quickly shake or stir to enjoy Matcha anytime, anywhere.       CONTAINS: 10 single-serving sticks (4g / stick).       Ceremonial Grade MatchaRich in AntioxidantsNo Sifting or Whisking       By blending Matcha with dietary fiber, we have eliminated the majority of Matcha clumping. Similar to our Ceremonial Matcha, Matcha To Go is intended to be used exclusively with water to enjoy the pure, smooth tea flavor.       All of Aiya’s Matcha is produced in the Nishio region of Aichi prefecture in Japan, where the finest Matcha has been grown for over 800 years. PREPARATION       COLD: Add contents of 1 stick to a 16.9 oz (500 ml) water bottle and shake until the Matcha is well mixed.HOT: Mix contents of 1 stick in 6-8 oz of hot water (180 °F). If desired, use an electric hand frother for foam. Aiya Matcha To Go stick packs are convenient and portable for the person on the go!', 21.99, 21.99, 'In Stock', 'Grocery & Gourmet Food › Beverages › Tea › Green › Matcha', '1.5 x 3.13 x 4.75 inches; 1.4 ounces', '2000-01-01', 'Aiya Matcha', null, 4.50, 1006, 77, 10, 6, 2, 5),
