        (886, 'IDO TEA Willowy tea 30 tea bags', 'IDOTEA Store', 'From the brand Previous page Background       The CEO of IDO has crafted a distinct range of fermented traditional teas, inspired by her personal journey with Narcolepsy and the guidance of a specialist in Korean traditional medicine. After successfully treating her condition with Korean herbal remedies, she was motivated to create a comprehensive collection of herbal teas that could be savored by all, without any unpleasant herbaceous odors or flavors. Why is IDO unique?       While many Asian tea companies choose to use traditional ingredients or produce fermented green tea, most brands do not ferment traditional tea ingredients. IDO, however, has dedicated years to cultivating their own crops and undergoing thorough research and development to create products that not only maximize nutritional value but are highly palatable, despite their bold choice of unfamiliar ingredients. Where is it produced?       IDOs herbs are harvested from a plantation in the idyllic town of ChungHaMeon, located in Pohang city, Korea. Nestled near a pine tree planted during the reign of King Sejong, the region is known for its pure and clear atmosphere, providing the perfect environment for nurturing high-quality herbs. IDO - What does it mean?       IDOs ingredients have been thoughtfully chosen by a highly respected herb specialist and Oriental wellness practitioner with over 17 years of experience, ensuring that our products provide the best possible support for your well-being. Next page Product Description Maintaining optimal wellness requires a balance between physical (posture and exercise), chemical (diet), and mental (stress and social) factors. However, in todays fast-paced world, it can be challenging to consistently consume fresh, home-cooked meals. IDO offers a solution with its tea adapted from ingredients traditionally used for wellness commonly, thus removing the potential for side effects or over consumption. By incorporating IDOs tea into your daily routine, you can easily absorb the nutrients your body needs to support a fit and nutritious lifestyle.       Experience the power of incremental improvement with a daily cup of tea! Organic Lotus Leaf                                      It is known to be abundant in Lectin and Vitamin A.       Organic lotus leaves picked from Haenam local farm are carefully fermented to give a smooth and deep flavor without leafy taste of a plant. Jeju Dwarf Bamboo                                      Harvested from Mount Halla in Jeju, stands for pure, clear and serenity. Tangerine Peel                                      On its peel, it contains more components than pulps. It is widely known for cleaning the waste in body. Mulberry Leaf                                      160x iron present in green tea and 10x GABA ingredient, full of nutrients. Flush out the Funk                                      The blend of these four ingredients is designed to support you when you feel greasy or uncomfortable stomach. Individually Packaged Non_GMO Tea Bags                                      IDO’s tea bags are Non-GMO and individually packed for convenient use and ease to take on-the-go. Organic                                      IDO’s manufacturing facility produces ORGANIC products of high quality. Long R&D for Quality Products                                      Not only have IDOs products been carefully chosen and developed by a professional Oriental wellness practitioner, but the company has also partnered with numerous research institutes specializing in the fermentation and advancement of fermented teas. During the aging process, the plants undergo fermentation using edible mold, similar to the process used in the creation of blue cheese. This allows for the solubilization of insoluble plant tissue.       The plants are then subjected to a second fermentation process, similar to the traditional method of crafting ginseng, through the repetitive steaming and drying of the plants to enhance their absorbability. Good Night Tea Breathing Tea Halo Flow Tea Purification Tea Enamor Tea Willowy Tea Add to Cart Buying Options Add to Cart Buying Options Add to Cart Add to Cart Customer Reviews 4.4 out of 5 stars 36 4.4 out of 5 stars 36 4.4 out of 5 stars 36 4.4 out of 5 stars 36 4.4 out of 5 stars 36 4.4 out of 5 stars 36 Price $15.00$15.00 —                 $15.00$15.00 —                 $30.00$30.00                  $30.00$30.00 Taste/Aroma Mild & Soothing              Comforting & Mild              Bold floral and fruity aroma              Soft & Mild              Deep & Soft              Slight Herbal scent & Earthy Depthful flavor Ingredients Jeju Dwarf Bamboo leaf, polygoni root              Balloon Flower Root, Lonicera Flower              Organic Lotus leaf               The Jeju Dwarf Bamboo leaf, kudzu root, Organic Tangerine Peel, Smilax china               Organic Tangerine Peel, Kudzu Root, Peony Root, and Scutellaria Root              Organic Lotus Leaf, Jeju Dwarf Bamboo, Tangerine Peel, Mulberry Leaf Function of support Better Sleep              Better breathing and good for seasonal changes              Calming effect              Purify and balance the body              Comfortable and clean body              Empty and cleans body tired from excessive habits Pack & Variation 15 tea bags/30 tea bags              15 tea bags              15 tea bags/30 tea bags              15 tea bags              30 tea bags              30 tea bags Non-GMO project verified ✓ ✓ ✓ ✓ ✓ ✓', 30.00, 30.00, 'Only 4 left in stock - order soon.', 'Grocery & Gourmet Food › Beverages › Tea › Fruit & Herbal Tea › Herbal', '5.91 x 1.18 x 8.27 inches; 2.19 ounces', '2000-01-01', 'IDO CO LTD', 'Korea, Republic of', 4.40, 36, 68, 16, 5, 10, 0),
        (887, 'Aiya Matcha To Go Single Serve Packs - Ceremonial Grade Pure Matcha Green Tea Powder (10 Count)', 'AIYA SINCE 1888 Store', 'From the brand Premium Japanese Matcha                                        Aiya Since 1888 Previous page High Quality VS. Low Quality Matcha       Taste:       The amino acids that give Matcha its sweet smell should actually make the tea taste slightly sweet, too.          Touch/Feel:       A high quality Matcha should feel very fine and silky similar to the feel of eye shadow or baby powder.       Lower quality matcha will have larger particle sizes that feel coarse between the fingers. High Quality VS. Low Quality Matcha          Color       Good quality Matcha is vibrantly green in color—often described as jade green—and lower qualities tend to have a more yellowish/brownish hue. High Quality VS. Low Quality Matcha          Price       Matcha is an expensive tea. Tons of labor goes into the cultivation, harvest, and manufacturing of Matcha          Smell:       A high quality Matcha should smell sweet and vegetal, thanks to the L-theanine amino acid that is preserved in the shade. Aiya Matcha         Store Loyalty & Dedication                                        Most of the tea farmers have worked exclusively with Aiya for multiple generations. Family owned and operated for over 130 years, Aiya is the world’s leading producer of Japanese Matcha green tea. Aiya is headquartered in the city of Nishio of Aichi Prefecture in central Japan, where the finest Matcha green tea has been grown for over 800 years. The company is currently managed by the 5th generation of the Sugita family with full-service sales and resource offices in 5 different countries across the world. Aiya is the largest producer of premium Japanese Matcha green tea. Based in Nishio, Japan, Aiya oversees all phases of the Matcha production process, from seed to bowl, and is committed to providing high-quality organic and conventional Matcha to the world. Aiya continually strives to improve product quality. As part of its commitment to transparency, Aiya undergoes annual third-party audits and holds multiple international certifications for its pure Matcha green tea. These certifications include: GFSI (FSSC 22000 by Bureau Veritas), AIB (Superior), JAS Organic by OMIC, NOP Organic by QAI, Halal, Kosher, Gluten-Free, and Non-GMO Project Verified. Next page Product Description Aiya’s Matcha To Go sticks pack a unique blend of traditional Ceremonial Grade Matcha into a convenient single-serving stick. Simply add one stick to cold or hot water, then quickly shake or stir to enjoy Matcha anytime, anywhere.       CONTAINS: 10 single-serving sticks (4g / stick).       Ceremonial Grade MatchaRich in AntioxidantsNo Sifting or Whisking       By blending Matcha with dietary fiber, we have eliminated the majority of Matcha clumping. Similar to our Ceremonial Matcha, Matcha To Go is intended to be used exclusively with water to enjoy the pure, smooth tea flavor.       All of Aiya’s Matcha is produced in the Nishio region of Aichi prefecture in Japan, where the finest Matcha has been grown for over 800 years. PREPARATION       COLD: Add contents of 1 stick to a 16.9 oz (500 ml) water bottle and shake until the Matcha is well mixed.HOT: Mix contents of 1 stick in 6-8 oz of hot water (180 °F). If desired, use an electric hand frother for foam. Aiya Matcha To Go stick packs are convenient and portable for the person on the go!', 21.99, 21.99, 'In Stock', 'Grocery & Gourmet Food › Beverages › Tea › Green › Matcha', '1.5 x 3.13 x 4.75 inches; 1.4 ounces', '2000-01-01', 'Aiya Matcha', null, 4.50, 1006, 77, 10, 6, 2, 5),
