        (918, 'Japanese Umeboshi Plum Paste with Shiso (8.8 oz/250g) - Pickled Plum, Gluten Free, Vegan, Plum Sauce Asian, Japanese Food, Onigiri, Sushi, Yakitori, Sashimi, Umeboshi Paste - Kinjirushi Wasabi', 'KINJIRUSHI BRAND Store', 'From the brand More than just Wasabi                                        Kinjiurshi Wasabi has an extensive line up of the most sought out Japanese condiments in the market that extend beyond the wasabi world Previous page Our logo consists of the character for gold (kin) stylized to resemble Mt. Fuji, the most symbolic and divine landmark in Japan, and the terraced fields in which wasabi is abundantly grown. This combination of Mt. Fuji and terraced fields symbolizes our highest quality of wasabi production. What other products do you carry?                                        Besides wasabi, we also carry ume (plum), garlic, ginger, sauces and our newest line up includes yuzu. What makes our products unique?                                        Although our company name includes wasabi, our love includes bringing great tasting Japanese food to customers around the world. We like to focus on quality instead of quantity making our products higher priced than our competitors but we take pride in our sourcing and manufacturing making sure we bring only the best to our customers table. Imported from japan Next page Product Description Same Great Taste                                             Brand New Look                                         Kinjirushi Wasabi Ume Paste with Shiso has gone through a makeover and now has a brand new look. But dont worry, we still have the same great taste. Umeboshi                                        Umeboshi is a dried and pickled fruit that resembles a plum but is actually a closer relative to the apricot. This salted and picked fruit is salty and sour at the same time. It is often used to eat with rice, noodles, rice balls (onigiri) and also can be used with alcohol as a flavor enhancer. Many people in Japan eat umeboshi as a cold remedy and has become a staple for many families in Japan. Japanese Nanko-Plum                                        Our ume paste is made from "Nanko-Ume" from the Kishu area of Japan which is known for their high quality plums. Largely harvested in the Wakayama Prefecture of Japan, these Nanko Umes are famous for their quality, their taste and their history. Wakayama Prefecture produces about 60% of Japans plum yield and has a history of over 60 years. Shiso Leaves                                        Shiso leaves, Perilla Leaves or Japanese basil is a aromatic herb that is often used with Sushi and Sashimi. There are 2 types of shiso leaves, green and red. Green shiso is used with many dishes as garnishes and can be eaten with a fresh, citrusy flavor with hints of mint, cloves and cinnamon. Red shiso tends to be a bit more bitter and is often used as a food dye, commonly used to dye Umeboshi and pickled ginger. How to Use                                                                                 Udon with Ume Paste                                                                                                                       Yakitori                                                                                                                    Lamb Chop with Ume Sauce                                                                                                                    Kale Salad with Ume Dressing Specifications                                                         Shelf Life:                                    400 days                                        Ingredients:                                    JAPANESE PLUM PASTE(JAPANESE PLUM,JAPANESE PLUM VINEGAR,SALT,SUGAR),BEEFSTAKEPLANT,WATER,HYDROGENATED STARCH SYRUP,CITRIC ACID,MODIFIED STARCH,ETHYLALCOHOL,STARCH,VEGETABLE JUICE,MONOSODIUM GLUTAMATE,VINEGAR,XANTHAN GUM,NATURAL ANDARTIFICIAL FLAVOR                                        Flavor:                                    Sour                                        Type:                                    Paste                                        Size:                                    8.8 oz or 250 g', 9.99, 9.99, 'In Stock', 'Grocery & Gourmet Food › Pantry Staples › Condiments & Salad Dressings › Wasabi', '2.55 x 1.65 x 7.04 inches; 8.82 ounces', '2000-01-01', 'Kinjirushi Wasabi', null, 4.40, 915, 69, 13, 7, 4, 5),
